            <title>[KAFKA-4077] Backdate validity of certificates in system tests to cope with clock skew</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4077</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The scenario described by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ewencp&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ewencp&quot;&gt;ewencp&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1483&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/1483&lt;/a&gt; where tests failed with java.security.cert.CertificateNotYetValidException. Certificates are created on the host and copied to VMs and hence should cope with a small amount of clock skew. Set start date to fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
